WEBVTT

01:46.739 --> 01:48.900
Attaboy! Keep him busy!

01:52.545 --> 01:54.012
One.
Jesus.

01:54.080 --> 01:55.570
Two.
You got it.

01:55.648 --> 01:57.240
Three.
He ain't getting up!

01:57.316 --> 02:01.776
Four, five, six

02:02.288 --> 02:07.248
seven, eight, nine, ten.

02:07.493 --> 02:08.925
Out!

02:12.965 --> 02:14.262
Come here, Jimmy.

02:14.800 --> 02:16.961
Get that sleeping beauty
out of here!

02:17.636 --> 02:19.763
That's ten in a row, Jimmy!
Ten!

02:19.839 --> 02:24.208
<i>By a knockout, at one minute 46 seconds
in the second round</i>

02:24.276 --> 02:26.039
<i>tonight's light
heavyweight winner</i>

02:26.112 --> 02:28.171
<i>from the great state
of New Jersey</i>

02:28.247 --> 02:31.705
<i>the Bulldog of Bergen,
James J. Braddock!</i>

02:42.762 --> 02:44.559
You're gonna be
the next champ, Jimmy!

02:44.630 --> 02:45.858
Hey, how you doing?

02:45.931 --> 02:47.558
Just give them a few.
Leave them wanting.

02:47.633 --> 02:49.032
You want to sign my name
for me, too?

02:49.101 --> 02:50.591
At least then
they can read it.

02:50.669 --> 02:51.829
You gave him
a cold meat party.

02:51.904 --> 02:53.132
Sign this for me,
Mr. Braddock.

02:55.508 --> 02:57.533
You've been getting
stronger with every fight.

02:57.610 --> 02:58.668
I've been seeing it.

02:58.744 --> 03:01.941
You may favor the right, sure, but
you got no stage fright or nerves.

03:02.014 --> 03:03.572
And you have never
been knocked out.

03:03.649 --> 03:05.879
You're in line.
That's all I'm saying, Jimmy.

03:05.951 --> 03:07.714
You're gonna get your shot.

03:08.454 --> 03:11.082
All right, let me see
what we got here.

03:11.524 --> 03:13.458
$886 for Jeanette

03:13.526 --> 03:15.357
$772 for Lou and Whitey

03:15.427 --> 03:20.296
$1,000 for the ring fees,
my $2,658 and your $3,544

03:20.366 --> 03:25.099
makes $8,860. Stick that
in your mattress, Irishman.

03:26.572 --> 03:28.904
When we get there, you gonna
come in and see the kids?

03:28.974 --> 03:31.465
It's been a while. Come on.
They miss their Uncle Joey.

03:31.544 --> 03:34.809
Yeah, that's very sweet. You
still married to the same girl?

03:35.881 --> 03:37.178
I was this morning.

03:37.249 --> 03:40.150
Well, congratulations.
Maybe I'll take a rain check.

03:40.219 --> 03:41.208
And would you tell her

03:41.387 --> 03:43.412
will you tell her I
undercharged on the gym fees

03:43.522 --> 03:45.854
and no load on the towel? Would
you do that for me, please?

03:45.925 --> 03:48.120
I will be sure to point
it out. I appreciate it.

03:48.194 --> 03:50.287
You stop up at the
corner here somewhere, Frank.

03:50.362 --> 03:53.058
Home to Jersey
for Mr. Adventure over here.

03:55.134 --> 03:57.159
All right, see you, Frank.

04:19.091 --> 04:20.887
I could kill you!

04:21.961 --> 04:24.259
I like the sound of that.

04:24.330 --> 04:26.628
Yeah, I like
the sound of that a lot.

04:27.132 --> 04:28.360
Jimmy.
Yeah?

04:28.434 --> 04:29.628
My sister.

04:30.569 --> 04:32.434
Daddy, did we win?

04:34.540 --> 04:35.734
Yeah, we won.

04:36.308 --> 04:37.866
How are you, Alice?

04:37.943 --> 04:39.808
Good. That's wonderful, Jimmy.

04:39.879 --> 04:41.107
Hey, Howard.

04:48.821 --> 04:50.152
Thank you.

04:50.556 --> 04:52.387
So tell me about him.

04:53.392 --> 04:55.292
Was he a real slugger?

04:57.363 --> 05:02.266
You know,
you could come and watch.

05:05.504 --> 05:08.166
No. You get hit

05:08.274 --> 05:11.869
every time, it feels
like I'm getting hit, too.

05:13.212 --> 05:15.908
And I'm not half as tough
as you are.

05:20.819 --> 05:22.980
So, tell me about the girls.

05:23.989 --> 05:25.149
Girls?

05:28.327 --> 05:30.261
I was at the Garden,
it was a fight night

05:30.329 --> 05:32.194
Come on. There was one.

05:32.898 --> 05:35.128
There must've been one.
No.

05:36.568 --> 05:38.559
Blond?
Brunette.

05:40.973 --> 05:42.270
Tall?

05:46.245 --> 05:48.110
Like a gazelle.

05:48.647 --> 05:51.207
I don't know how it is
she breathed up there.

05:51.717 --> 05:53.742
Mr. Braddock!

05:54.987 --> 05:58.582
You're so strong!

05:59.425 --> 06:04.021
And your hands,
they're so big.

06:04.596 --> 06:06.928
You're so powerful!

06:11.403 --> 06:15.100
Jimmy, I'm so proud of you.

06:15.841 --> 06:17.502
I'm so proud of you.

06:20.813 --> 06:22.405
Introducing

06:22.481 --> 06:26.440
two-time state Golden Gloves
title holder

06:26.652 --> 06:29.780
in both the light heavyweight
and heavyweight divisions

06:29.855 --> 06:33.814
21-0, with 16 wins
coming by way of knockout

06:34.026 --> 06:38.554
the Bulldog of Bergen,
the pride of New Jersey

06:38.897 --> 06:40.728
and the hope of the Irish

06:40.799 --> 06:44.291
as the future champion
of the world

06:44.370 --> 06:48.067
James J. Braddock.

07:22.875 --> 07:25.139
Ma, you woke me up.

07:25.944 --> 07:28.378
Well, you
kicked the covers off, honey.

07:29.048 --> 07:31.243
Now you go back to sleep,
all right?

07:31.784 --> 07:33.376
Good night, Mom.

07:33.452 --> 07:35.079
Good night, sweetheart.

08:40.519 --> 08:42.248
I can't find my socks.

08:42.488 --> 08:44.615
Jim!
I'm sorry.

08:45.691 --> 08:47.056
Mama?

08:48.360 --> 08:51.261
Great.
I'm sorry, baby.

08:51.363 --> 08:54.491
I washed them last night.
Took them right off your feet.

08:54.800 --> 08:56.665
Don't you remember?
No.

08:59.705 --> 09:01.730
Well, you were out
like a light.

09:09.314 --> 09:11.339
How do I keep them this warm?

09:11.917 --> 09:14.351
Mama, I want to eat, too.

09:15.254 --> 09:17.222
Mommy will get you some,
honey.

09:20.325 --> 09:24.022
Hey, Rosy-Rosy.
Good morning, good morning.

09:27.933 --> 09:31.130
Got a notice yesterday.
Gas and electric.

09:32.838 --> 09:34.066
Come on.

09:34.206 --> 09:37.539
Okey-dokey, there we go.
I'll get the milk.

10:02.601 --> 10:04.796
Well, I think
there's some left over.

10:07.206 --> 10:08.332
Yep.

10:09.007 --> 10:11.805
You know, I got that
fight tonight at the armory.

10:13.845 --> 10:16.575
Yeah, one guy, Abe Feldman.

10:16.815 --> 10:18.680
That's $50, win or lose.

10:18.850 --> 10:20.283
That's good.

10:21.520 --> 10:24.216
If I beat him, maybe I can get
my purses back up to $75.

10:24.289 --> 10:26.018
That would be great.

10:27.426 --> 10:30.987
Rosy, use your fork, please.

10:33.432 --> 10:35.229
Who needs a cow, huh?

10:36.301 --> 10:38.201
Mama, I want some more.

10:39.738 --> 10:42.969
I'm sorry, sweetheart. We
need to save some for the boys.

10:47.312 --> 10:48.779
Here you go.

10:49.681 --> 10:52.445
You know, Mae,
I dreamed last night

10:52.684 --> 10:54.879
that I was having dinner
at The Ritz.

10:55.087 --> 10:56.782
With Mickey Rooney
and George Raft.

10:56.855 --> 10:57.947
Really!
Yeah.

10:58.023 --> 11:01.982
And I dreamed I had a steak.
A thick, juicy steak.

11:02.294 --> 11:03.522
Like this, Rosy.

11:04.329 --> 11:06.661
And then I had a mountain
of mashed potatoes

11:06.732 --> 11:09.166
and I went back for ice cream
three times.

11:10.202 --> 11:11.635
I'm stuffed.

11:12.137 --> 11:14.867
I'm absolutely full.
I cannot eat another thing.

11:16.108 --> 11:18.008
Want to give me a hand?

11:18.477 --> 11:19.637
Jim.

11:46.338 --> 11:48.966
Boys, hurry up. Don't dawdle.

11:49.107 --> 11:50.938
Let's try and sleep
a little more.

12:00.052 --> 12:02.020
<i># Sure, business is bunk #</i>

12:02.087 --> 12:04.248
<i># And Wall Street is sunk #</i>

12:04.323 --> 12:06.314
<i># We're all of us broke #</i>

12:06.391 --> 12:08.416
<i># And ready to croak #</i>

12:08.493 --> 12:10.484
<i># We've nothing to dunk #</i>

12:10.562 --> 12:12.530
<i># Can't even get drunk #</i>

12:12.597 --> 12:16.431
<i># And all the while
they tell us to smile #</i>

12:16.902 --> 12:18.995
<i># Cheer up, gentle citizens #</i>

12:19.071 --> 12:20.971
<i># Though you have no shirts #</i>

12:21.039 --> 12:23.132
<i># Happy days are here again #</i>

12:23.208 --> 12:25.267
<i># Cheer up, smile, nertz #</i>

12:25.344 --> 12:27.369
<i># All aboard prosperity #</i>

12:27.446 --> 12:29.346
<i># Giggle till it hurts #</i>

12:29.414 --> 12:31.473
<i># No more breadline charity #</i>

12:31.550 --> 12:33.575
<i># Cheer up, smile, nertz #</i>

12:33.652 --> 12:35.643
<i># Sunny smilers we must be #</i>

12:35.721 --> 12:37.552
<i># The optimist asserts #</i>

12:37.622 --> 12:39.988
<i># Let's hang
the fathead to a tree #</i>

12:40.058 --> 12:42.026
<i># Cheer up, smile, nertz ##</i>

12:44.596 --> 12:47.463
I need nine men and only nine.

12:48.033 --> 12:51.525
One. Two. Three.

12:52.604 --> 12:56.802
Four. Five. Six.

13:01.146 --> 13:05.810
Seven. Eight. Nine. That's it!

13:07.185 --> 13:09.176
All right, let's get a move on!

13:10.789 --> 13:14.316
Go on, get going!
Got a lot of work today!

13:30.909 --> 13:32.433
Hey, Dad.
Hey.

13:32.544 --> 13:35.342
No shifts today, Dad?
What're you doing, son?

13:35.414 --> 13:38.247
I'm being good. I'm being
quiet. I'm being 'hayve.

13:38.517 --> 13:39.609
Great.

13:40.685 --> 13:41.982
Daddy!

13:43.622 --> 13:45.715
Hey, Rosy-cheeks.
How you doing?

13:45.791 --> 13:47.759
Daddy, Jay stole!

13:48.160 --> 13:50.219
What?
Jay stole.

14:00.071 --> 14:02.130
What's all this about?
See? It's a salami.

14:02.207 --> 14:04.300
Young lady, your brother's
in enough trouble

14:04.376 --> 14:06.867
without you telling on him.
You understand?

14:08.146 --> 14:09.511
It's from the butcher's.

14:09.581 --> 14:12.141
And he won't say a word
about it, will you, Jay?

14:12.217 --> 14:13.479
Will you, Jay?

14:17.956 --> 14:19.753
Okay, pick it up. Let's go.

14:22.294 --> 14:25.058
Do not test me, boy.
Right now.

14:31.269 --> 14:32.668
Howard, stay here.

14:39.211 --> 14:41.941
Okay, let's go! Come
on, give me a hand here!

14:48.720 --> 14:50.278
Great,
then you don't get paid!

14:50.355 --> 14:51.322
Bye.

14:58.163 --> 15:00.154
Don't forget to
pick it up easy!

15:03.568 --> 15:07.527
Marty Johnson had to go away to
Delaware to live with his uncle.

15:08.874 --> 15:09.932
Why?

15:10.308 --> 15:13.277
His parents didn't have
enough money for them to eat.

15:19.150 --> 15:22.608
Yeah, well, things ain't easy
at the moment, Jay, you're right.

15:23.555 --> 15:26.615
But there's a lot of people
worse off than what we are.

15:29.561 --> 15:31.461
And just 'cause
things ain't easy

15:31.530 --> 15:34.522
that don't give you the excuse
to take what's not yours, does it?

15:34.599 --> 15:37.500
That's stealing, right?
And we don't steal.

15:37.802 --> 15:40.168
No matter what happens,
we don't steal.

15:40.539 --> 15:42.564
Not ever. You got me?

15:49.014 --> 15:51.346
Are you giving me your word?
Yes.

15:52.551 --> 15:54.576
Go on.
I promise.

15:59.090 --> 16:00.853
And I promise you

16:02.661 --> 16:05.027
we will never send you away.

16:10.869 --> 16:12.336
It's okay, kid.

16:13.305 --> 16:15.569
You got a little scared.
I understand.

16:16.508 --> 16:17.600
It's okay.

16:37.896 --> 16:40.729
Jim, he's a very slow guy.

16:41.099 --> 16:42.794
Just plants himself there.

16:42.867 --> 16:45.199
So you just keep him steady.

16:45.270 --> 16:48.569
Keep him trapped in the middle.
Keep dancing around him, okay?

16:50.075 --> 16:52.441
You know what to do.
You know this type.

16:53.678 --> 16:55.111
That guy's a bum.

17:01.252 --> 17:03.243
Two bits will
get a guy a seat.

17:04.055 --> 17:07.183
And that guy gets to watch
you bleed and call you a bum.

17:08.492 --> 17:12.156
And I know I gotta take it from
him, 'cause he's a paying customer.

17:13.198 --> 17:14.597
I see.

17:15.433 --> 17:17.025
Well, well, well.

17:17.902 --> 17:22.066
Pardon me, miss. Allow
me to restate my position.

17:23.742 --> 17:27.405
Mr. Abraham Feldman
is a novice fighter

17:27.479 --> 17:30.175
whose ass you should
gently kick

17:30.248 --> 17:33.046
until it is humped up
between his shoulder blades.

17:33.952 --> 17:36.819
That is, if it doesn't offend
your overly sensitive nature.

17:36.888 --> 17:38.253
God knows.

17:51.169 --> 17:53.569
Now, you see, that break's
still a few weeks away.

17:53.638 --> 17:54.969
I know.
Yeah.

17:55.040 --> 17:56.905
And you were gonna tell me
about this when?

17:56.975 --> 17:59.773
It's gonna be fine. It's
not fine. No, it's not.

17:59.844 --> 18:01.038
What the hell?
You don't tell me?

18:01.112 --> 18:04.411
What the hell kinda crap is
that? I owe everybody money, Joe.

18:07.152 --> 18:08.710
I can't get any shifts.

18:08.787 --> 18:10.652
We ain't got any cash.

18:13.792 --> 18:15.589
I got it.

18:19.564 --> 18:21.862
Screw them.
I'll tape it double.

18:23.334 --> 18:24.528
Thanks.

18:26.304 --> 18:28.431
Keep up. Stay up.

18:28.840 --> 18:31.331
Keep moving.
Keep your legs moving.

18:33.011 --> 18:34.444
<i>And here comes Braddock</i>

18:34.512 --> 18:36.605
<i>with his long-time manager,
Joe Gould.</i>

18:36.681 --> 18:38.478
You're washed up, Braddock.

18:38.850 --> 18:40.442
<i>And now for our main event.</i>

18:40.518 --> 18:41.610
Hey, which one's us, pal?

18:41.686 --> 18:42.846
<i>Jersey veteran
James J. Braddock</i>

18:42.921 --> 18:45.412
<i>is up against Hymie Caplin's
latest charge</i>

18:45.490 --> 18:47.856
<i>young Abe Feldman
from Schenectady, New York.</i>

18:47.926 --> 18:48.915
Six rounder.

18:48.993 --> 18:51.086
<i>Some might recall
that Braddock was once</i>

18:51.162 --> 18:53.596
<i>a light heavyweight
title challenger.</i>

18:53.665 --> 18:56.828
<i>His golden-boy peak ended
when Tommy Loughran</i>

18:56.901 --> 19:00.667
<i>handled Jim over 15 rounds
back in '29.</i>

19:00.739 --> 19:02.866
<i>Since then,
the oft-injured Braddock</i>

19:02.941 --> 19:05.808
<i>has shown only a glimmer
of his early promise.</i>

19:05.877 --> 19:08.505
<i>And the losses have started
to pile up.</i>

19:08.580 --> 19:10.946
<i>But Braddock continues
to battle.</i>

19:11.883 --> 19:14.681
<i>And here comes
the popular Abe Feldman.</i>

19:14.753 --> 19:16.550
<i>Feldman looks to be
the real thing</i>

19:16.621 --> 19:20.717
<i>and showed some real moxie
in his recent win over Hans Birkie.</i>

19:23.962 --> 19:26.226
Hey, who whipped Latzo?

19:27.232 --> 19:28.665
I did.
Goddamn right.

19:28.733 --> 19:30.530
Who KO'ed Slattery
in the ninth

19:30.602 --> 19:34.129
when everybody said he didn't
have a rainmaker's chance in hell?

19:34.539 --> 19:36.063
That'd have to be me, too.
Right.

19:36.141 --> 19:38.974
And we're supposed to pucker our
assholes over this Abe Feldman?

19:39.043 --> 19:40.977
The guy couldn't break wind.
No.

19:41.479 --> 19:42.844
Hey, Jimmy.

19:44.482 --> 19:46.814
Anyplace else you'd rather be?

19:46.885 --> 19:48.216
No.
Good.

19:48.453 --> 19:50.444
Now, what are you
gonna do about it?

19:51.723 --> 19:54.021
<i>Here we are halfway
through the fifth</i>

19:54.092 --> 19:55.787
<i>And it's more of the same.</i>

19:55.860 --> 19:57.521
<i>The boys clinch again.</i>

19:57.595 --> 19:58.584
Break it up.

19:58.663 --> 20:00.494
He's crushing my guy. Get him off!

20:00.698 --> 20:02.723
Break!

20:02.967 --> 20:05.026
<i>The boo-birds
have started flying here.</i>

20:05.103 --> 20:07.298
<i>They want action
from these fighters.</i>

20:07.405 --> 20:09.498
<i>Feldman sticks a left
in Braddock's face.</i>

20:09.574 --> 20:12.168
<i>Braddock's right hand
is his best and only weapon.</i>

20:12.243 --> 20:15.007
<i>He'll show the left, but it lacks snap
and Feldman knows it.</i>

20:15.079 --> 20:17.639
Come on, give these yokels
a shot in the ass!

20:18.483 --> 20:21.714
<i>Feldman ducks a haymaker
but fails to follow up.</i>

20:29.460 --> 20:31.291
<i>And another big right
by Braddock.</i>

20:31.362 --> 20:33.296
<i>Now, there's the Braddock
we all recall.</i>

20:33.364 --> 20:35.992
<i>But it's one at a time.
It may not be enough.</i>

20:37.268 --> 20:38.360
Come on!

21:06.097 --> 21:07.860
<i>The referee pulls
the boys apart.</i>

21:07.932 --> 21:10.059
<i>And there's the bell
to end the fifth.</i>

21:10.134 --> 21:11.999
Easy now. Easy.

21:13.972 --> 21:17.408
I saw that.
You bust it again?

21:18.042 --> 21:19.805
I'm calling it, Jim.

21:23.715 --> 21:26.013
You gonna use the left?
Okay, good.

21:26.084 --> 21:28.245
You get in there but you
don't let him crowd you.

21:28.319 --> 21:30.549
You work his belly, you
hammer his belly with the left.

21:30.622 --> 21:32.988
Last round. Come on,
you got to show me something.

21:33.057 --> 21:35.150
Give me a good one. You're
giving me an ulcer, Harry!

21:35.226 --> 21:36.284
Shut up.

21:36.494 --> 21:38.792
Work his belly with the left.
You got it?

21:38.863 --> 21:41.593
Give him the flapdoodle with
the right because he don't know.

21:41.666 --> 21:43.634
Right?
'Cause he's kind of stupid.

21:43.701 --> 21:45.498
Okay? Last round.

21:45.970 --> 21:47.301
Last round! Go get him!

21:48.039 --> 21:49.734
The left!

21:51.609 --> 21:54.305
Damn it, I wish he could find
his goddamn left.

21:55.346 --> 21:57.314
That's it! Change it up!

21:57.916 --> 21:59.406
Southpaw, that's it!

21:59.484 --> 22:02.044
<i>Feldman prancing around,
looking for an opening</i>

22:02.120 --> 22:04.782
<i>but still few clean punches
by the fighters.</i>

22:04.856 --> 22:07.256
<i>Braddock still pawing away
with the left.</i>

22:07.892 --> 22:10.122
<i>Another ineffectual left
from Feldman.</i>

22:10.194 --> 22:13.994
<i>Braddock can hardly lift his arms.
He's slow on his feet.</i>

22:14.065 --> 22:16.829
<i>At least Gould in his corner
is still throwing punches</i>

22:16.901 --> 22:18.766
<i>trying to urge his man on.</i>

22:22.307 --> 22:23.706
Go home!

22:29.280 --> 22:30.440
Go home, Braddock!

22:31.716 --> 22:33.274
No holding, Braddock!

22:33.351 --> 22:35.911
<i>Cavanaugh's working harder
than the fighters.</i>

22:36.955 --> 22:38.183
Dry up!

22:40.825 --> 22:41.951
<i>Another clinch.</i>

22:42.026 --> 22:45.962
<i>It's as if 80 tough fights
have finally jumped on Braddock's back.</i>

22:46.864 --> 22:48.627
You're a bum!

22:54.973 --> 22:55.997
That's it!

22:56.074 --> 22:58.099
<i>Cavanaugh pulls them apart,
and he's called the fight.</i>

22:58.176 --> 22:59.507
<i>He's called the fight.</i>

23:00.311 --> 23:02.006
<i>It's a "no contest. "</i>

23:02.080 --> 23:05.777
<i>And the popcorn and the peanuts
are raining down.</i>

23:05.850 --> 23:09.308
<i>And I'm afraid to say that's all these
fighters deserve</i>

23:09.387 --> 23:11.480
<i>for the show
they put on tonight.</i>

23:13.591 --> 23:17.083
<i>I'm telling you, it's sad to see
a fighter that was once</i>

23:17.161 --> 23:19.789
<i>the caliber of James Braddock
reduced to this.</i>

23:19.864 --> 23:21.456
It's all right, Jimmy.

23:23.935 --> 23:25.402
An embarrassment,
that's what it was.

23:25.470 --> 23:26.767
An embarrassment!

23:26.838 --> 23:28.237
Where the hell's the purse?

23:28.306 --> 23:29.933
You wouldn't have
to be asking that

23:30.008 --> 23:31.976
if you gave a shit
about your fighter.

23:32.043 --> 23:35.376
Okay. He's fighting hurt.

23:35.847 --> 23:38.509
Maybe you got a bunch of fat
and happy fighters at home

23:38.583 --> 23:41.575
can afford to rest a month between
bouts. I don't know. Lucky you!

23:41.652 --> 23:44.120
Christ, he hardly gets
a punch in anymore!

23:44.455 --> 23:47.549
Fights being stopped by
referees? He's pathetic!

23:48.393 --> 23:50.520
Fights like
that keep people away.

23:54.032 --> 23:55.556
We're revoking his license,
Joe.

23:56.901 --> 24:00.359
Whatever Braddock was gonna do
in boxing, I guess he's done it.

24:00.705 --> 24:03.538
Wait a minute.
That's all.

24:09.247 --> 24:10.475
Oh, boy.

24:16.020 --> 24:17.419
Mr. Johnston!

24:19.624 --> 24:20.682
Jim.

24:21.626 --> 24:23.218
What's going on?

24:23.928 --> 24:26.556
You didn't tell him?
Yeah, of course I told him.

24:26.631 --> 24:28.292
He wanted to
hear it from you.

24:28.366 --> 24:30.459
Come on, Mr. Johnston,
no contest?

24:30.902 --> 24:33.632
I broke my hand.
Okay? It's legit.

24:33.905 --> 24:35.998
You don't see me
crying about it.

24:36.441 --> 24:38.341
I don't see what you got
to complain about.

24:38.409 --> 24:42.175
I still went out there, I still put
on a show. I did what I could do.

24:42.747 --> 24:44.612
You know, we did that
boondock circuit for you

24:44.682 --> 24:46.206
me and Joe. Remember?

24:48.186 --> 24:51.121
I didn't quit on you.
And I didn't quit tonight.

24:53.658 --> 24:55.353
I didn't always lose.

24:55.593 --> 24:57.390
I won't always lose again.

24:58.229 --> 25:00.459
I can still fight.
Go home.

25:00.531 --> 25:03.557
I can still fight. Go home
to Mae and the kids, Jim.

25:05.536 --> 25:07.629
Go home? Go home with what?

25:08.306 --> 25:12.800
Go home with what? A broken
hand from Mount Vernon?

25:14.712 --> 25:16.407
Mr. Johnston!

25:50.915 --> 25:52.007
Baby?

26:00.858 --> 26:02.450
What happened?

26:03.427 --> 26:05.122
I didn't get the dough.

26:06.297 --> 26:07.924
They didn't pay up.

26:10.001 --> 26:13.698
They called it a "no contest,"
said the fight was an embarrassment.

26:15.239 --> 26:16.831
They decommissioned me.

26:20.945 --> 26:22.469
Jimmy,
what happened to your hand?

26:22.547 --> 26:24.742
It's broke again
in three places.

26:25.883 --> 26:27.407
They said I'm through, Mae.

26:27.485 --> 26:29.544
They said
I can't be a boxer no more.

26:29.620 --> 26:31.087
Mercy.

26:36.394 --> 26:37.486
Okay.

26:43.100 --> 26:44.931
Jimmy, if you can't work

26:45.002 --> 26:48.165
we're not gonna be able to pay
the electric, or the heat.

26:53.511 --> 26:55.877
And we're out of credit
at the grocery.

26:59.083 --> 27:01.347
So I think we need
to pack the kids.

27:02.153 --> 27:04.621
They could stay at my sister's
for a little while

27:04.689 --> 27:07.817
and I'll take in more sewing.

27:07.892 --> 27:09.519
That way we could make
two, three breadlines a day.

27:09.594 --> 27:11.118
I'll get doubles, triples,
whatever I can find.

27:11.195 --> 27:13.493
Jimmy, you can't work.
Mae, I can still work.

27:13.564 --> 27:16.055
Jimmy, you can't work.
Your hand's broken.

27:18.202 --> 27:19.567
They see me
lugging this around,

27:19.637 --> 27:20.797
you're right,
they won't pick me.

27:20.871 --> 27:22.964
Not down the docks,
not anywhere.

27:24.742 --> 27:26.403
So we're gonna cover it up

27:26.477 --> 27:28.104
with the shoe polish.

27:30.314 --> 27:31.474
Okay?

27:58.409 --> 28:01.037
I'm sorry.
No.

28:06.917 --> 28:08.077
No.

28:18.663 --> 28:19.652
No.

28:40.084 --> 28:42.917
I need five and only five!

28:43.421 --> 28:45.286
Come on, Jake!

28:46.691 --> 28:48.056
One.

28:49.927 --> 28:51.224
Two.

28:53.864 --> 28:55.297
Three.

28:56.901 --> 28:58.095
Four.

29:01.172 --> 29:03.299
Five. That's it!

29:18.189 --> 29:20.384
What the hell
happened to your face?

29:20.791 --> 29:22.691
I got in a fight.
Yeah?

29:22.993 --> 29:24.790
What'd you go do that for?

29:25.730 --> 29:27.357
That's a good question.

29:28.299 --> 29:29.698
Mike Wilson.

29:30.634 --> 29:31.931
Jim Braddock.

29:32.503 --> 29:35.529
I used to follow a pretty good
fighter with that name.

29:37.942 --> 29:40.877
And there's some other guy
going around using that name now.

29:40.945 --> 29:42.845
Can't fight for shit.

29:42.913 --> 29:46.246
Gambling man will lose
a lot of money on him. Twice.

29:53.691 --> 29:55.556
That hand ain't gonna work.

29:55.626 --> 29:57.958
You can't slow me down.
I need this job.

29:59.230 --> 30:00.697
I need the job, too.

30:09.640 --> 30:12.165
What's wrong with
the goddamn hand?

30:20.818 --> 30:22.979
You see us
falling behind, Jake?

30:24.989 --> 30:26.388
He's all right.

30:34.465 --> 30:35.830
Appreciate it.

30:39.136 --> 30:40.933
I'll get a cold beer.

30:41.472 --> 30:42.996
Just a water for me, Quincy.

30:43.073 --> 30:45.507
All I got today
are big spenders.

30:45.576 --> 30:47.510
Beer for him, too. I'm buying.

30:48.879 --> 30:50.471
Don't hurt my feelings.

30:50.548 --> 30:53.813
It's been a while, but You
don't have to twist my arm.

30:56.287 --> 30:59.984
Yeah, I used to be a
broker. Still lost it all in '29.

31:00.424 --> 31:01.789
Yeah, me, too.

31:02.726 --> 31:05.627
I had just about everything
I ever earned in stocks.

31:06.096 --> 31:07.927
Even had a little
taxi company.

31:07.998 --> 31:11.399
I mean, who loses their dough
on cabs in New York City, right?

31:11.569 --> 31:14.595
Well, I thought that one
was gold for the grandkiddies.

31:14.672 --> 31:17.539
You know, there's people living
in shacks in Central Park.

31:17.608 --> 31:19.303
Call it the Hooverville.

31:19.543 --> 31:21.773
This government's
dropped us flat.

31:21.846 --> 31:25.407
We need to organize, you know?
Unionize. Fight back.

31:26.617 --> 31:28.380
Fight? Fight what?

31:28.452 --> 31:30.818
Bad luck? Greed? Drought?

31:31.789 --> 31:33.416
No point punching things
you can't see.

31:33.491 --> 31:35.721
No, we'll work
a way through this.

31:35.793 --> 31:38.489
FDR, he's gonna handle it.
Screw FDR.

31:38.829 --> 31:41.024
FDR, Hoover,
they're all the same.

31:41.098 --> 31:43.794
You know, I come home one day.
I stand in my living room.

31:43.868 --> 31:46.860
And between the mortgage and the
market and the goddamn lawyer

31:46.937 --> 31:48.734
that was supposed
to be working for me

31:48.806 --> 31:50.569
it stopped being mine.

31:51.642 --> 31:53.542
It all stopped being mine.

31:54.411 --> 31:57.141
FDR ain't given me
my house back yet.

32:03.187 --> 32:05.815
Mama, why can't I
go to school?

32:05.890 --> 32:07.824
Is it because I'm a girl?

32:08.559 --> 32:11.323
Maybe. Hadn't thought of that.

32:16.534 --> 32:18.661
Who's that man
at our house?

32:20.604 --> 32:22.071
Excuse me!

32:25.109 --> 32:26.736
Can I help you?

32:26.944 --> 32:28.673
I'm sorry, lady,
you're past due.

32:28.746 --> 32:31.112
No, you can't.

32:31.181 --> 32:33.240
You can't.
There's kids.

32:34.018 --> 32:35.815
If I
don't, they let me go.

32:36.820 --> 32:39.448
They already let two guys go.
Please.

32:40.291 --> 32:44.387
This apartment, it's what we got
left that keeps us hanging on.

32:44.595 --> 32:46.358
Lady, I got kids, too.

32:57.608 --> 32:58.973
$6.74.

32:59.877 --> 33:01.708
How much to turn it back on?

33:03.781 --> 33:07.217
Four months. $44.12.

33:13.457 --> 33:17.154
If I work 26 hours out of
every 24, it still won't add up.

33:23.467 --> 33:26.561
We ain't got nothing.
Nothing left to sell.

33:32.242 --> 33:34.506
All the guys
you could've married, huh?

33:36.647 --> 33:40.208
Yeah.
What happened to those guys?

34:01.605 --> 34:02.867
It's Howard.

34:04.775 --> 34:06.333
Since this afternoon.

34:15.252 --> 34:16.981
"Bless us, O Lord

34:17.353 --> 34:20.083
"and these thy gifts which
we are about to receive

34:20.157 --> 34:21.715
from thy bounty. "

34:28.565 --> 34:30.032
I'm all prayed out.

34:41.445 --> 34:43.106
Here's more firewood.

34:50.054 --> 34:54.047
Where are you going?
I said where are you going?

34:55.259 --> 34:58.456
Go to hell,
you no-good bastard!

34:58.529 --> 35:01.589
Go on, then!
We don't need you!

35:01.665 --> 35:05.123
All right. Help me,
pick up some of that wood.

35:05.202 --> 35:07.500
I got it, Mama.
All right, let's go, sweetheart.

35:07.571 --> 35:08.936
All right, honey.

35:15.813 --> 35:17.906
Nice and warm, huh?

35:23.420 --> 35:24.546
Baby?

35:26.657 --> 35:27.646
Baby?

35:28.092 --> 35:29.582
Look at Mommy.

35:35.332 --> 35:36.697
Sweetheart.

35:45.142 --> 35:46.336
Mommy?

35:52.149 --> 35:53.309
What's wrong?

35:55.385 --> 35:57.182
Nothing, sweetheart.

35:57.788 --> 36:00.120
Mommy will be right back,
okay?

36:54.578 --> 36:59.015
Howard's fever was getting worse
and then Rosy started to sneeze.

37:11.128 --> 37:13.995
Where are they, Mae? Jim,
we can't even keep 'em warm.

37:15.933 --> 37:17.093
Where are the kids?

37:18.135 --> 37:21.002
The boys will sleep on the
sofa at my father's in Brooklyn.

37:21.071 --> 37:22.766
And Rosy'll stay
at my sister's.

37:22.840 --> 37:24.501
Jimmy, we can't keep 'em!

37:24.575 --> 37:27.237
You don't make decisions
about our children without me.

37:27.311 --> 37:30.280
What if they get really sick?
We already owe Dr. McDonald

37:30.347 --> 37:32.372
If you send them away, then
all this has been for nothing!

37:32.449 --> 37:34.644
It's just until we get back
What else was it for?

37:34.718 --> 37:36.913
If we can't stay together,
that means we lost!

37:36.987 --> 37:39.080
That means we've given up!
I am not giving up!

37:39.156 --> 37:41.989
I'm trying to protect our
children. Mae, I promised him.

37:43.026 --> 37:44.391
Outside the butcher's.

37:44.461 --> 37:45.450
I looked him in the eyes

37:45.529 --> 37:47.087
and I promised him
with all of my heart

37:47.164 --> 37:49.564
I would never ever
send him away.

37:51.501 --> 37:52.991
You can't do this.

37:53.871 --> 37:55.031
You weren't here.

37:56.073 --> 37:57.563
You can't break my promise.

37:59.409 --> 38:02.606
Jim, you didn't see.
You weren't here.

38:11.955 --> 38:13.047
I'm sorry.

38:17.527 --> 38:18.824
I'm sorry, Jimmy.

38:22.599 --> 38:24.362
What are you doing?

38:28.972 --> 38:30.234
Jim?

38:31.341 --> 38:34.799
Jimmy! Where you going?

38:36.780 --> 38:38.304
Where you going, Jimmy?

38:57.901 --> 39:00.495
That doesn't qualify you,
sir. What else can you tell me?

39:00.570 --> 39:03.061
The problem is my wife
is losing all of her teeth.

39:03.140 --> 39:04.698
I got a relief order
for her.

39:04.775 --> 39:07.039
The doctor says
it's due to insufficient diet.

39:07.110 --> 39:09.408
She's still nursing the baby
on account of

39:09.479 --> 39:11.106
we can't afford milk
for the family.

39:11.181 --> 39:12.307
Okay.

39:23.927 --> 39:26.054
I never thought
I'd see you here, Jim.

40:37.701 --> 40:39.259
He jumped up

40:39.536 --> 40:41.595
kicked his stool
out of the ring

40:42.706 --> 40:44.298
and he was just,
he was furious.

40:44.374 --> 40:45.500
I grabbed the mike

40:52.249 --> 40:54.080
There's Jimmy Braddock.

41:01.058 --> 41:02.923
The thing is,
I can't afford to

41:04.694 --> 41:05.922
I can't afford
to pay the heat.

41:07.030 --> 41:08.622
I've had to
farm out my kids.

41:09.900 --> 41:12.562
You know, they keep cutting
shifts down at the docks

41:12.669 --> 41:14.728
and you just don't get picked
every day.

41:18.442 --> 41:20.967
I sold everything I've got
that anybody would buy.

41:28.718 --> 41:31.710
I went on public assistance. I
signed on at the relief office.

41:32.422 --> 41:35.880
They gave me $19.
I need another $18.38

41:35.959 --> 41:38.951
so I can pay the bill
and get the kids back.

41:43.300 --> 41:46.792
You know me well enough to know
if I had anywhere else to go

41:48.371 --> 41:49.565
I wouldn't be here.

41:54.044 --> 41:57.207
If you could help me through this
time, I sure would be grateful.

42:09.893 --> 42:11.258
Sure, Jim. Sure.

42:19.436 --> 42:20.596
Good luck.

42:21.771 --> 42:22.999
Jim.

42:27.244 --> 42:28.506
Hey, Jimmy.

42:58.041 --> 42:59.406
Here you go, Jim.

43:00.944 --> 43:02.206
Good luck, Jim.

43:24.601 --> 43:27.126
I'm sorry, Joe, I didn't
I'm sorry.

43:29.506 --> 43:31.838
What in the hell do you have
to be sorry about?

43:32.642 --> 43:34.303
Jesus Christ, Jimmy.

43:41.651 --> 43:43.084
How short are you?

43:54.931 --> 43:56.455
About $1.50.

43:59.469 --> 44:00.561
Okay.

44:03.073 --> 44:04.904
We're home! Hooray, we're home!

44:05.208 --> 44:06.641
We're glad to be home!

44:09.980 --> 44:11.072
Good.

44:18.822 --> 44:19.948
Okay. All right.

44:20.824 --> 44:24.658
Howard, don't jump on
the bed. Sorry, Mama.

44:25.262 --> 44:26.593
Read to me, Jay.

44:27.397 --> 44:29.388
"On his way up
and down the stairs "

44:29.466 --> 44:32.458
Do you like being
home? I like being home, too.

44:33.570 --> 44:35.128
My little doll.

44:37.774 --> 44:41.039
<i># Happy birthday to you #</i>

44:45.415 --> 44:49.283
<i># Happy birthday,
dear Howard #</i>

44:51.788 --> 44:55.087
<i># Happy birthday to you ##</i>

44:55.392 --> 44:56.689
Make a wish, kids.

44:56.893 --> 44:57.985
Blow!

45:03.066 --> 45:05.694
Hey, Howard, come on.
They're gonna cut the cake up.

45:05.835 --> 45:06.995
You wanna line up, huh?

45:07.504 --> 45:09.665
You looking forward
to some chocolate cake?

45:09.773 --> 45:11.707
I liked it better
when we had our own.

45:11.908 --> 45:13.239
I can understand that.

45:17.314 --> 45:18.975
Hiya, Howard. Hi.

45:19.182 --> 45:21.946
Hey, your dad ever tell you
that I used to spar with him?

45:22.686 --> 45:25.246
You hit the Father?
As often as I possibly could.

45:25.789 --> 45:28.280
He was kinda tricky, though.
Hard to catch.

45:28.525 --> 45:30.015
Go and get some cake. Go on.

45:31.428 --> 45:32.827
Missed you at mass, Jimmy.

45:33.563 --> 45:35.827
I can get an extra shift
on a Sunday, you know?

45:35.899 --> 45:37.764
Don't you walk
away from me! James.

45:37.834 --> 45:38.926
Mike, you hear me?

45:39.002 --> 45:40.094
Excuse me.

45:40.170 --> 45:43.037
Every day, "fix the world. "
How about fixing your family?

45:43.106 --> 45:44.539
What kind of father
are you?

45:44.607 --> 45:47.770
Too proud to cross the street
because she can't have her own cake?

45:47.844 --> 45:50.312
And now you're drunk at
church, for Christ's sake.

45:50.380 --> 45:53.508
That a joke, Sara? Making a
joke? I'm just saying it's enough!

45:53.583 --> 45:56.313
Guys, where's the ref? Why
don't you stay out of this?

45:56.386 --> 45:59.355
It's between man and wife. How
do you even call yourself that?

45:59.422 --> 46:00.411
What'd you say to me?
Come on.

46:00.490 --> 46:01.514
Get your hands off me!

46:01.591 --> 46:02.649
You've had a couple drinks.
It's Sunday.

46:02.726 --> 46:05.126
No harm in that. Day of rest.
All washed up. Can't get a fight.

46:05.195 --> 46:06.355
What, you want to fight me?

46:06.429 --> 46:07.760
Mike,
you don't have to do this.

46:07.831 --> 46:09.093
I ain't got no beef
with you.

46:09.165 --> 46:11.531
Come on! Can't make it in the ring, huh?

46:12.135 --> 46:14.296
Come on, Braddock,
I'll take your head off!

46:15.071 --> 46:18.529
Jim, no!
Mike, you okay, baby?

46:19.542 --> 46:20.975
Why don't you get off me?

46:21.511 --> 46:23.376
Go to hell! The both of you!

46:24.381 --> 46:26.212
Jesus, Jim,
he wasn't gonna hit me.

46:28.818 --> 46:30.376
Mike, wait!

46:41.297 --> 46:44.391
Now, what it's all about is
rotating your body behind your fist.

46:44.467 --> 46:46.594
Bang. That's right.
Right in the kisser, yeah.

46:48.671 --> 46:49.660
There you go.

46:52.442 --> 46:55.741
Good girl. You got a
better jab than your dad.

46:57.714 --> 47:01.480
Boy, you are a brave man. Not
really. Mae's at the store.

47:02.952 --> 47:04.442
That's a good one, kiddo!

47:04.521 --> 47:07.115
You want to go play with the other
kids while I talk to Uncle Joe?

47:09.626 --> 47:13.062
Joe Gould,
still looking dapper, I see.

47:13.363 --> 47:16.264
Certainly. Gotta keep up
appearances, right?

47:17.867 --> 47:20.199
Good to see you, Jimmy.
Nice to see you, Joe.

47:21.871 --> 47:23.395
Nice day, huh?

47:24.507 --> 47:25.838
Yeah.

47:28.044 --> 47:30.774
You drove all the way out here
to talk about the weather?

47:30.847 --> 47:33.611
Maybe I was in the neighborhood.
Did you ever think of that?

47:33.683 --> 47:34.843
Little fresh air.

47:35.618 --> 47:37.643
Joe, this is Jersey.

47:39.656 --> 47:41.055
Yeah. Good point.

47:46.362 --> 47:47.590
I got you a fight.

47:49.332 --> 47:51.357
Go to hell. Come on.
You want it, don't you?

47:51.434 --> 47:54.665
What, we gonna bring this up with
the Boxing Commission, or not?

47:54.737 --> 47:57.865
Yes, and they'll sanction it.
This one fight, and one fight only.

47:57.941 --> 48:00.466
It's not a comeback, right?
It's just one fight.

48:01.244 --> 48:03.109
Why?
'Cause of who you're fighting.

48:03.446 --> 48:04.504
How much?

48:04.581 --> 48:06.071
Just once, ask me who
it is you're fighting.

48:06.149 --> 48:08.515
How much?
$250.

48:08.751 --> 48:11.481
You're on at the big show
at the Garden, tomorrow night.

48:11.554 --> 48:13.784
You fight Corn Griffin, Jimmy.

48:13.857 --> 48:15.950
Number two heavyweight
contender in the world.

48:16.025 --> 48:17.754
Prelim before
the championship bout.

48:17.827 --> 48:20.022
You know, Joe, this
ain't funny. No, it's not.

48:20.096 --> 48:22.030
And it ain't no favor,
either.

48:22.098 --> 48:24.464
Griffin's opponent got cut,
and he couldn't fight.

48:24.534 --> 48:27.162
So they had to find somebody they
could throw in at a day's notice.

48:27.237 --> 48:28.568
Nobody legit would

48:31.441 --> 48:34.274
Nobody would take a fight
with Griffin without training.

48:35.378 --> 48:39.508
So I told them use the angle
Griffin's gonna knock out a guy

48:40.283 --> 48:41.614
never been knocked out.

48:42.819 --> 48:44.013
You're meat, Jimmy.

48:44.487 --> 48:45.784
Are you on the level, Joe?

48:45.855 --> 48:47.550
Come on. Always.

48:47.891 --> 48:49.859
For $250,
I would fight your wife.

48:50.860 --> 48:51.849
Now you're dreaming.

48:51.928 --> 48:53.691
And your grandmother.
At the same time.

48:53.763 --> 48:55.128
Teeth in or teeth out?
Take them out.

48:55.198 --> 48:56.722
Then you're dead.
You're down, you're gone.

48:56.799 --> 48:57.891
No chance.
$250?

48:57.967 --> 48:59.264
250 bananas. Come here.

49:03.773 --> 49:05.536
Get your programs here!

49:08.011 --> 49:10.445
Programs here! 25 cents!

49:11.814 --> 49:14.942
I mean, for Christ's sake,
100 and something fights

49:15.018 --> 49:16.485
you never been knocked out.

49:16.553 --> 49:18.453
Who the hell goes
and sells his gear?

49:19.122 --> 49:21.113
80 fights as a pro,
50 as an amateur.

49:21.958 --> 49:24.825
How soon they forget!
I'm so sorry.

49:24.928 --> 49:27.954
Borrowed gear, borrowed robe.
Knock yourself out.

49:30.133 --> 49:31.191
Joe.

49:35.338 --> 49:38.432
I might as well get an Aooga horn
and chase him around the ring.

49:40.476 --> 49:43.240
That's good.
You been drinking?

49:43.313 --> 49:45.144
Are you trying to
hurt my feelings?

49:45.415 --> 49:48.612
You're just too loose. You're
spooking me. Sharpen up.

49:48.685 --> 49:51.779
Come on, Joe, we both
know what this is, right?

49:52.889 --> 49:56.188
I get to put a little more distance
between my kids and the street

49:56.593 --> 49:59.494
and I get to say good-bye
at the Garden.

50:01.397 --> 50:03.194
Full house,
night of a big fight.

50:04.534 --> 50:05.865
Thank you very much.

50:06.102 --> 50:08.002
Right. Come on, hurry up.

50:08.338 --> 50:09.930
Let's get the lead
out of here.

50:13.409 --> 50:14.774
What the hell was that?

50:15.878 --> 50:18.176
They ran out of soup
on the line this morning.

50:18.247 --> 50:20.306
Ran out of soup
on the line this morning.

50:20.383 --> 50:23.284
How the hell are you supposed
to fight on an empty stomach?

50:23.820 --> 50:25.185
<i>Good evening.</i>

50:25.254 --> 50:30.021
<i>Welcome to tonight's broadcast
of the Primo Carnera/Max Baer fight</i>

50:30.293 --> 50:32.784
<i>for the heavyweight
championship of the world!</i>

50:33.496 --> 50:36.556
Hash is all they had, okay?
Eat, quick.

50:37.166 --> 50:39.726
You got a spoon? For
Christ's sake, it's not there?

50:39.802 --> 50:42.032
Come on, we gotta go anyway.
One bite, Joe.

50:42.105 --> 50:44.073
I'll eat it with my fingers.
Whoa, hey!

50:44.507 --> 50:46.270
I don't have time
to re-tape you.

50:46.576 --> 50:49.443
Just sit tight,
and I'll find you a spoon.

50:51.147 --> 50:52.580
For Christ's sake.

51:04.027 --> 51:06.495
Is that a ghost
I'm seeing? An apparition?

51:06.562 --> 51:09.759
Or is that James J. Braddock,
the Bulldog of Bergen?

51:10.066 --> 51:12.534
How you feeling, Jimmy?
How's that right hand?

51:12.602 --> 51:14.001
Braddock, you're up!

51:19.809 --> 51:22.209
Sporty Lewis, how you doing?
How you doing?

51:24.681 --> 51:27.741
July 18, 1929.

51:29.152 --> 51:30.278
<i>New York Herald.</i>

51:32.321 --> 51:34.448
"Proving he was too young
and too green

51:35.391 --> 51:36.722
"and rushed to the top

51:38.594 --> 51:41.062
"Loughran wiped the ring
with the Bulldog's career.

51:42.065 --> 51:43.589
"A sad and somber funeral

51:45.068 --> 51:46.797
with the body
still breathing. "

51:47.737 --> 51:50.865
I don't fight the fights, Jimmy,
I just write about them, see?

51:50.940 --> 51:53.500
Sporty, save the crap
for the customers.

52:05.421 --> 52:06.581
Who's Jim Braddock?

52:06.656 --> 52:09.523
Go get your pencil out, kid.
I got your lead line for you.

52:09.592 --> 52:11.787
Go ahead, I'm not kidding,
write this down.

52:12.161 --> 52:15.130
"The walk from the locker room
to the ring

52:15.198 --> 52:18.326
was the only time tonight
old Jim Braddock "

52:18.401 --> 52:19.925
Looking good, Jimmy!

52:20.303 --> 52:22.237
" was seen on his feet. "
You got that?

52:22.305 --> 52:24.773
<i>Before tonight's championship
battle, we'll bring you</i>

52:24.841 --> 52:27.605
<i>a special bout featuring
Charlie Harvey's soldier boy</i>

52:27.977 --> 52:29.308
<i>Corn Griffin.</i>

52:29.378 --> 52:31.039
<i>Griffin is the fella
that ran rings</i>

52:31.114 --> 52:33.241
<i>around the champion Carnera
in training.</i>

52:33.483 --> 52:34.882
<i>And who's his opponent?</i>

52:34.951 --> 52:38.079
<i>Looks like they dug old Jim Braddock
out of retirement</i>

52:38.154 --> 52:39.587
<i>at least for one more fight.</i>

52:39.789 --> 52:41.450
<i>Hey, Mike! Griffin is up
in the ring now.</i>

52:41.524 --> 52:43.754
<i>Braddock? Isn't that your buddy?
Look at the size of him!</i>

52:44.560 --> 52:46.755
<i>In this corner</i>

52:48.397 --> 52:52.094
<i>the sensational
heavyweight slugger</i>

52:52.168 --> 52:54.261
<i>from Fort Benning, Georgia</i>

52:54.737 --> 52:58.195
<i>who is punching a path
to the top of the division.</i>

52:58.708 --> 53:01.336
<i>John "Corn" Griffin!</i>

53:05.014 --> 53:08.973
<i>His opponent:
The popular battler</i>

53:09.051 --> 53:13.215
<i>who has never been KO'ed in more than
80 professional bouts</i>

53:13.956 --> 53:15.184
Quincy, beer. We got a fight!

53:15.258 --> 53:16.452
<i>the power-punching
veteran</i>

53:16.526 --> 53:19.051
<i>from North Bergen,
New Jersey</i>

53:19.796 --> 53:22.424
<i>James J. Braddock!</i>

53:47.924 --> 53:49.915
<i>The skinny from
the reporters at ringside</i>

53:49.992 --> 53:52.017
<i>is that Braddock
won't last two rounds.</i>

53:52.094 --> 53:54.585
<i>Griffin is a five-to-one
favorite to do just that.</i>

53:54.664 --> 53:57.189
<i>But Joe Gould claims
Braddock's right hand is fine.</i>

53:57.266 --> 53:59.257
<i>Jimmy will need
two good hands tonight.</i>

54:04.974 --> 54:06.839
<i>Griffin storms out
of his corner!</i>

54:07.210 --> 54:09.269
<i>Things are up-tempo right away.</i>

54:12.415 --> 54:14.315
Come on, Braddock,
make a fight of it!

54:21.490 --> 54:23.617
Get out of it! Get out, Jimmy!

54:23.726 --> 54:25.489
<i>Braddock takes a left
to the body</i>

54:25.561 --> 54:26.755
<i>and a hard right to the head!</i>

54:26.829 --> 54:28.490
<i>Braddock's giving ground now.</i>

54:28.865 --> 54:29.957
<i>A hard right!</i>

54:30.032 --> 54:31.590
<i>Pins him in
the neutral corner.</i>

54:32.001 --> 54:33.662
Get outta there, Jim! Get out!

54:33.736 --> 54:34.725
<i>Griffin's all over him!</i>

54:35.671 --> 54:37.161
<i>Braddock taking hard jabs.</i>

54:39.775 --> 54:41.265
<i>And Braddock is down.</i>

54:41.544 --> 54:43.512
Shut up! I wanna hear this!
Shut up!

54:44.380 --> 54:47.747
Jim? You're fine. Stay down.

54:56.359 --> 54:58.725
One. Two.
Stay down! What's the hurry?

54:58.794 --> 55:01.058
Three. Four.
Hey! Listen.

55:01.130 --> 55:03.564
I liked the left. Try two lefts. Five.

55:03.633 --> 55:04.895
Give him two lefts!
Six.

55:04.967 --> 55:06.901
Pop, pop! Double it up.
Seven.

55:06.969 --> 55:08.937
How 'bout it? Up, up.
Eight.

55:09.005 --> 55:10.632
What the hell are you doing?
Let's go.

55:10.706 --> 55:11.695
Nine.

55:12.108 --> 55:14.099
Yeah, come on, Jimmy!
On your feet, come on!

55:15.344 --> 55:17.608
<i>The referee waving Griffin in.</i>

55:18.281 --> 55:19.270
Move in on that.

55:19.348 --> 55:20.679
Nice move!

55:21.384 --> 55:23.045
Bring him in!

55:24.787 --> 55:26.084
<i>Snaps a stiff jab! Another!</i>

55:27.957 --> 55:29.618
Welcome to New York.

55:29.692 --> 55:31.592
Beautiful!

55:32.194 --> 55:34.094
That's more like it!
Let me see that cut.

55:34.697 --> 55:36.130
You look great!

55:36.933 --> 55:39.800
It sure as hell beats working
on the docks!

55:41.437 --> 55:45.134
Say, the two jabs look
sensational! They look sweet!

55:45.508 --> 55:47.635
Now, he's loading up on you.
You see that?

55:47.710 --> 55:50.838
He opens up after you jab him. You
gotta come in there with a right.

55:50.913 --> 55:51.902
Real quick.

55:52.882 --> 55:55.077
But you gotta stop
some of those left hands.

55:56.052 --> 55:57.952
You see any
getting past my head?

55:58.454 --> 55:59.512
Keep moving!

56:03.426 --> 56:05.155
<i>Griffin still winging
big shots.</i>

56:05.227 --> 56:07.354
<i>He wants to be the first
to stop Braddock.</i>

56:09.532 --> 56:11.557
<i>Braddock gets in
another big right hand!</i>

56:11.667 --> 56:13.828
<i>Snapped Griffin's head back
with that one.</i>

56:15.538 --> 56:16.903
Come on!

56:16.973 --> 56:18.304
<i>Griffin loading up.</i>

56:21.444 --> 56:23.105
Move out!
Give him the slip, Jimmy!

56:23.179 --> 56:25.010
<i>Another big flurry by Griffin!</i>

56:25.081 --> 56:28.744
<i>Braddock hanging tough but, folks,
he is taking a beating!</i>

56:30.987 --> 56:33.615
That's two rounds more
than I thought he was gonna go.

56:34.256 --> 56:36.554
He's a half a step behind you.
Do you feel it?

56:37.693 --> 56:39.593
Stick with it.

56:39.829 --> 56:40.955
Busy, busy.

56:42.798 --> 56:44.925
<i>Six minutes of fury so far.</i>

56:45.668 --> 56:48.796
<i>Braddock has the look of a man
trying to hold back an avalanche.</i>

56:51.440 --> 56:53.340
<i>Griffin hits him with a left.</i>

56:53.409 --> 56:55.400
<i>And Braddock is stepping
in post holes.</i>

56:57.980 --> 56:59.572
Keep him in front of you!

57:01.283 --> 57:02.375
Lure him in, Jim.

57:02.952 --> 57:04.783
<i>Jimmy's finally
moving his head.</i>

57:06.455 --> 57:08.013
Pick your spot!

57:17.133 --> 57:18.430
<i>And Griffin is down!</i>

57:23.873 --> 57:26.137
Where the hell have you been,
Jimmy Braddock?

57:26.976 --> 57:30.173
One. Two. Three.

57:30.646 --> 57:32.113
<i>He's up at three.</i>

57:32.381 --> 57:34.008
<i>The referee wipes his gloves.</i>

57:41.690 --> 57:44.887
That's it!
No daylight!

57:45.127 --> 57:46.651
Take it to him!

57:47.063 --> 57:48.792
<i>Another big right by Braddock!</i>

57:48.931 --> 57:50.398
Finish him, Jimmy!

57:57.706 --> 58:00.402
Knock him back
to the goddamn Ozarks!

58:02.978 --> 58:04.411
<i>Griffin is ready to go!</i>

58:06.348 --> 58:07.713
Be careful.

58:08.017 --> 58:09.382
Get back.

58:10.019 --> 58:12.510
Get back there.
Get back in your corner.

58:17.793 --> 58:18.987
Jimmy!

58:22.598 --> 58:25.066
<i>This fight is over!
This is incredible!</i>

58:25.134 --> 58:27.967
<i>Corn Griffin, the number two
contender in the world</i>

58:28.037 --> 58:31.495
<i>has just been knocked out
by Jim Braddock in the third round!</i>

58:31.574 --> 58:32.905
<i>What an upset!</i>

58:32.975 --> 58:34.670
You son of a bitch!

58:34.743 --> 58:36.938
<i>It's pandemonium here
in the Garden!</i>

58:37.012 --> 58:39.446
That's it, man, he did it!
I don't believe it!

58:41.517 --> 58:43.576
You beautiful bastard!

58:45.421 --> 58:47.218
Settle down, for Christ's sake!

58:49.625 --> 58:51.217
Jesus H. Christ!

58:51.961 --> 58:55.658
Jesus, Mary and Joseph,
Mary Magdalene

58:55.731 --> 58:58.598
all the saints and martyrs
and Jesus!

58:59.368 --> 59:00.995
Did I say "Jesus"?

59:02.204 --> 59:03.671
Where the hell did
that come from?

59:03.739 --> 59:05.229
I don't know.
When my hand was broke

59:05.307 --> 59:07.571
I had to work down on the
docks and I had to use my left.

59:07.643 --> 59:10.510
So, what?
No, that and luck.

59:10.579 --> 59:12.672
Luck?
Sheer dumb-ass Irish luck.

59:12.748 --> 59:15.012
Don't give me that
luck-of-the-Irish crap. No, sir.

59:15.084 --> 59:18.144
Lucky? That's something you ain't
been in a long time, brother.

59:18.387 --> 59:19.513
Everybody's due.

59:19.588 --> 59:21.385
Due or not, I'll take it.
You had the left.

59:21.457 --> 59:23.220
The left. But you were bouncy.

59:23.659 --> 59:25.923
You were bouncing.

59:27.563 --> 59:31.499
Unbelievable. Sliding,
slipping. You were like a cat.

59:31.567 --> 59:32.966
I did that on hash.

59:33.569 --> 59:36.663
Imagine what I would've done to
him if I'd had a couple of steaks.

59:38.374 --> 59:39.534
Jimmy?

59:40.976 --> 59:42.705
That was one hell of
a good-bye.

59:49.952 --> 59:52.352
Here you go, fellas!
Have at him!

01:00:23.485 --> 01:00:25.146
Jesus Christ!

01:00:28.424 --> 01:00:30.085
Murder him, Maxie!

01:00:31.827 --> 01:00:33.294
Primo!

01:00:34.263 --> 01:00:35.321
This is fighting?

01:00:35.397 --> 01:00:38.093
Why doesn't he just hit him
with a goddamn chair?

01:00:41.537 --> 01:00:43.630
Griffin was supposed to fight
Baer next.

01:00:44.373 --> 01:00:47.308
He should kiss your ass for
saving him from that thing.

01:01:08.597 --> 01:01:10.326
Throw him down, Maxie!

01:01:11.133 --> 01:01:12.998
Give it to him, Maxie!

01:01:27.049 --> 01:01:28.710
<i>Ladies and gentlemen</i>

01:01:28.784 --> 01:01:31.947
<i>the new heavyweight champion
of the world</i>

01:01:32.021 --> 01:01:33.488
<i>Max Baer!</i>

01:01:46.568 --> 01:01:48.297
Come on! He's home.

01:02:16.865 --> 01:02:18.025
I won.

01:02:19.435 --> 01:02:22.370
Hooray, he won! I knew you'd win!

01:02:25.574 --> 01:02:27.565
He won, he won, he won!

01:02:31.280 --> 01:02:33.043
Get the silverware.

01:02:34.717 --> 01:02:38.448
So was it like you said? Or
are they letting you back in?

01:02:41.423 --> 01:02:43.152
No, baby.
It was just one fight.

01:02:57.740 --> 01:03:00.675
All right, I need
seven men, and seven only!

01:03:01.310 --> 01:03:04.973
One. Two. Three.

01:03:09.685 --> 01:03:12.017
Four. Five.

01:03:14.890 --> 01:03:16.084
Thanks.

01:03:17.326 --> 01:03:18.588
Braddock!

01:03:25.334 --> 01:03:27.427
Listened in last night.
Was that really you?

01:03:30.739 --> 01:03:31.763
Yeah.

01:03:31.840 --> 01:03:33.808
Didn't think
I'd be seeing you back here.

01:03:33.876 --> 01:03:35.776
It came up at the last minute,
you know?

01:03:35.878 --> 01:03:38.278
It was a one-fight deal.
The purse was $250.

01:03:38.347 --> 01:03:41.282
My end of that was a little less
than half. It was, like, $123.

01:03:41.350 --> 01:03:43.409
We owed $118.
Left me with $5.

01:03:44.119 --> 01:03:46.019
Makes you a rich man, huh?
Around here.

01:03:46.789 --> 01:03:48.723
Good fight.
Thanks.

01:03:49.258 --> 01:03:50.623
Dock seven.
Seven.

01:03:56.865 --> 01:03:58.696
Hey, Jim.
Hey, Mike.

01:04:04.606 --> 01:04:06.369
Good fight.
Thanks.

01:04:11.947 --> 01:04:14.472
I wouldn't have hit Sara.
I know, Mike.

01:04:14.883 --> 01:04:17.113
I couldn't live with myself
if I'd have hit her.

01:04:19.888 --> 01:04:21.879
Just get so angry
with all this shit.

01:04:25.761 --> 01:04:29.492
You know, if you were gonna
win, you could've told me.

01:04:29.898 --> 01:04:32.458
If I knew I was gonna win,
I would've bet on myself.

01:04:33.101 --> 01:04:36.070
Why can't you ever listen
to me? I don't know.

01:04:37.005 --> 01:04:39.701
<i>to determine whether
the strikers were willing</i>

01:04:39.775 --> 01:04:41.936
<i>to submit to
an arbitration situation.</i>

01:04:42.678 --> 01:04:45.374
<i>Tension pervaded the New York
waterfront yesterday.</i>

01:04:46.548 --> 01:04:48.573
Why don't you go play
with the boys, sweetheart?

01:04:48.650 --> 01:04:49.639
Be careful.

01:04:52.187 --> 01:04:53.950
Hey, Rosy.
Hi, Daddy!

01:04:59.862 --> 01:05:02.990
You know,
Joe Gould was just here.

01:05:03.398 --> 01:05:04.797
Yeah, I saw.
You did?

01:05:07.703 --> 01:05:12.072
He thinks the Commission
might be willing to

01:05:12.908 --> 01:05:14.341
reverse their ruling.

01:05:14.409 --> 01:05:16.343
He thinks he can get me
another fight.

01:05:17.112 --> 01:05:20.047
He wants me to stop working
and get back in shape.

01:05:21.617 --> 01:05:23.551
I thought it was
just the one fight.

01:05:24.887 --> 01:05:26.252
Well, yeah.

01:05:30.325 --> 01:05:33.522
He fronted us $175
so I can train.

01:05:36.498 --> 01:05:38.295
You know what that is
right there?

01:05:38.567 --> 01:05:40.000
That's a second chance.

01:05:41.503 --> 01:05:42.868
That's what that is.

01:05:46.508 --> 01:05:48.806
It's not that
I'm not grateful

01:05:50.646 --> 01:05:53.911
or proud, honey.
I'm so proud of you.

01:05:55.984 --> 01:05:58.919
But we got off easy
when you broke that hand.

01:06:00.622 --> 01:06:01.953
We're back to even now.

01:06:02.024 --> 01:06:05.016
Right. And nine months from
now, we're back in the same boat.

01:06:05.093 --> 01:06:06.321
Baby, please.

01:06:06.595 --> 01:06:09.029
We just don't have anything
left to risk.

01:06:09.097 --> 01:06:10.257
Mae.

01:06:11.967 --> 01:06:15.164
There's still some juice in these
legs, and I can still take a few.

01:06:15.837 --> 01:06:16.963
Baby, please.

01:06:19.541 --> 01:06:21.532
Just let me take them
in the ring.

01:06:21.610 --> 01:06:23.407
At least I know
who's hitting me.

01:06:40.696 --> 01:06:42.357
I'm gonna go
and tell the kids.

01:06:43.365 --> 01:06:45.765
Jay! Guess what.
What?

01:06:46.602 --> 01:06:49.002
I got another fight!
Who with?

01:06:49.071 --> 01:06:52.563
I don't know, but he's
going down. Hey, Howard.

01:07:31.146 --> 01:07:32.306
Jesus.

01:07:34.483 --> 01:07:35.950
Joe, open the door.

01:07:38.654 --> 01:07:40.622
Joe! Open the damn door!

01:07:41.023 --> 01:07:44.686
Don't hide in your fancy
apartment. I want to talk to you.

01:07:46.361 --> 01:07:50.161
You are not gonna make my husband
your punching bag all over again.

01:07:50.232 --> 01:07:52.826
We are just getting by, and
you're taking him from his work

01:07:52.901 --> 01:07:55.165
like some bloodsucking
little leech!

01:07:55.404 --> 01:07:58.100
And I will not let you get
him hurt again like that

01:07:58.173 --> 01:08:00.698
do you hear me?
I will not let you!

01:08:04.346 --> 01:08:05.779
Guess you better come in.

01:08:17.759 --> 01:08:19.090
How is it?

01:08:19.294 --> 01:08:21.057
Too sweet per usual.

01:08:21.395 --> 01:08:23.057
Really? Go figure.

01:08:23.865 --> 01:08:25.729
Yours? Nice, thanks.

01:08:28.537 --> 01:08:29.697
Sorry about that.

01:08:32.674 --> 01:08:35.142
You just don't want folks
to see you down is all.

01:08:36.178 --> 01:08:38.372
I didn't know.
I mean, I thought that

01:08:38.447 --> 01:08:43.009
Yeah, no. That's the idea.
Always keep your hands up.

01:08:50.192 --> 01:08:52.126
Sold the last of it
two days ago.

01:08:53.295 --> 01:08:54.557
So Jimmy could train.

01:08:55.796 --> 01:08:57.024
Why?

01:09:03.205 --> 01:09:05.469
Sometimes you have
an instinct, Mae.

01:09:06.408 --> 01:09:08.535
You see something
in a fighter.

01:09:11.078 --> 01:09:14.571
You don't even know if it's real,
you're looking for it so bad.

01:09:22.424 --> 01:09:23.857
Can't have no hope at all.

01:09:25.227 --> 01:09:26.421
But this is crazy.

01:09:26.495 --> 01:09:29.191
I mean, you don't even know
if you can get him a fight.

01:09:29.264 --> 01:09:30.629
I'll get him a fight.

01:09:30.698 --> 01:09:33.691
Believe me, if it's the last
thing I do, I'll get him a fight.

01:09:33.769 --> 01:09:36.237
Honey. Go get us some
of those crackers, would you?

01:09:38.540 --> 01:09:40.337
She looks good
wearing the pants.

01:09:54.856 --> 01:09:56.551
Can you ever stop yours?

01:09:57.926 --> 01:09:59.723
When he sets his mind
to a thing?

01:10:04.132 --> 01:10:05.656
I wish I could.

01:10:07.903 --> 01:10:09.803
See, I never know
who it's harder on

01:10:10.272 --> 01:10:11.432
them or us.

01:10:12.307 --> 01:10:14.775
We have to wait for them
to fix everything.

01:10:17.679 --> 01:10:18.941
And every day

01:10:22.250 --> 01:10:24.047
they feel like
they're failing us.

01:10:25.453 --> 01:10:28.183
And really, it's just the
world that's failed, you know?

01:10:35.263 --> 01:10:38.994
This is a lovely apartment. Thank you.

01:10:42.404 --> 01:10:44.429
Now, what am I
gonna go and do that for?

01:10:44.873 --> 01:10:46.568
You saw the papers.

01:10:46.641 --> 01:10:49.667
<i>News had to print extra
copies the day after Braddock's fight.</i>

01:10:49.744 --> 01:10:52.838
People are sentimental, you
know. Some people are sentimental.

01:10:52.914 --> 01:10:54.404
Yeah, so tell me why I care.

01:10:55.817 --> 01:10:58.911
You're still sore over the way
Braddock took down Griffin, fine.

01:10:58.987 --> 01:11:02.013
I can understand that. It was a
heartbreak for a lot of people.

01:11:02.090 --> 01:11:03.717
Yes. But look.

01:11:07.362 --> 01:11:09.421
You got guys fighting
an elimination series

01:11:09.497 --> 01:11:12.591
over who gets a shot at Max Baer
for the championship in June.

01:11:12.934 --> 01:11:15.425
John Henry Lewis,
he's your number two in line.

01:11:15.503 --> 01:11:18.529
Now, he already defeated
Braddock once in Frisco, correct?

01:11:19.674 --> 01:11:22.541
Say you put Braddock back
in the game against Lewis.

01:11:22.611 --> 01:11:25.102
Lewis wins, you get your
revenge on Braddock

01:11:25.180 --> 01:11:27.478
and your boy has gotten
a topflight tune-up

01:11:27.549 --> 01:11:30.143
with full publicity before
Lasky, and what happens?

01:11:30.218 --> 01:11:31.708
You make more money.

01:11:34.956 --> 01:11:38.949
Now, say on the other hand, by
some minute, infinitesimal chance

01:11:39.027 --> 01:11:40.995
God forbid,
Braddock beats Lewis.

01:11:41.062 --> 01:11:42.859
Now you got a sentimental
favorite go up

01:11:42.931 --> 01:11:45.195
and lose against Lasky,
and what happens?

01:11:45.267 --> 01:11:46.928
You'll make more money.

01:11:47.469 --> 01:11:49.130
James, either way

01:11:49.204 --> 01:11:52.640
you're a richer man with Braddock
back in the ring than if he's not.

01:11:52.908 --> 01:11:56.275
Come on, don't be foolish. We
both know the name of this game.

01:11:58.146 --> 01:12:00.011
And it sure as hell
ain't "pugilism. "

01:12:12.661 --> 01:12:15.323
They ought to put your mouth
in a circus.

01:12:16.464 --> 01:12:18.091
What do you say?

01:12:19.868 --> 01:12:22.234
Don't chase him.
Go around, cut him off.

01:12:23.071 --> 01:12:24.163
Time! James!

01:12:26.341 --> 01:12:28.275
I got you a fight.
Yeah?

01:12:28.343 --> 01:12:30.573
You're gonna fight
John Henry Lewis again.

01:12:30.645 --> 01:12:31.805
Yeah!

01:12:31.880 --> 01:12:33.370
Joey! I could kiss you!

01:12:33.448 --> 01:12:35.882
No, please,
not in front of the fellas.

01:12:36.117 --> 01:12:38.449
Isn't John Henry
one of Johnston's boys?

01:12:38.653 --> 01:12:40.314
You let me worry about that,
please.

01:12:40.388 --> 01:12:43.516
Now I know why you won't kiss me.
You're all puckered out already.

01:12:44.192 --> 01:12:45.659
Brother, you have no idea.

01:12:46.094 --> 01:12:48.790
Lewis?
Kicked our ass in Frisco.

01:12:48.863 --> 01:12:51.127
Yeah. Hey, Mike.
Who's "our ass" up there?

01:12:51.199 --> 01:12:53.326
Joe Gould, Mike Wilson.
Mike Wilson, Joe Gould.

01:12:53.401 --> 01:12:54.527
Hi.

01:12:54.602 --> 01:12:56.536
That guy ain't been beat
in ten fights.

01:12:56.604 --> 01:12:59.630
But you win on a long shot, and
that's a great payday for me.

01:13:00.642 --> 01:13:02.701
That's great.
I'll keep that in mind, Mike!

01:13:02.777 --> 01:13:05.644
You got more important things
to think about. Come here.

01:13:06.314 --> 01:13:09.010
Now, I ain't gonna
bullshit you, all right?

01:13:09.517 --> 01:13:11.576
Now, you win one,
I can get you another.

01:13:11.653 --> 01:13:15.714
Win again and then things maybe
start getting serious around here.

01:13:16.291 --> 01:13:17.451
Jimmy?

01:13:19.060 --> 01:13:20.118
Win.

01:13:36.811 --> 01:13:37.903
Look good.

01:13:40.015 --> 01:13:41.312
Leverage.

01:13:50.725 --> 01:13:52.215
That's it, James!

01:13:52.293 --> 01:13:55.126
Be a bully, James!
Aggression, that's it.

01:14:17.218 --> 01:14:18.344
Thanks.

01:14:20.822 --> 01:14:22.687
I know this isn't
what you wanted

01:14:23.091 --> 01:14:25.025
but I can't win
without you behind me.

01:14:26.428 --> 01:14:27.759
I'm always behind you.

01:14:28.963 --> 01:14:30.555
Thank you, baby.

01:14:33.134 --> 01:14:35.602
I got a great idea.
You want to come along?

01:14:36.037 --> 01:14:39.370
Come on, just this one time.
All right. Okay.

01:14:39.441 --> 01:14:41.739
Okay, I'll make that
a rain check then.

01:15:09.571 --> 01:15:12.472
<i>Lewis, still moving well here
in the fourth.</i>

01:15:12.841 --> 01:15:15.469
<i>He dances in and out
before Braddock can react.</i>

01:15:19.147 --> 01:15:21.081
Don't let him
set the pace, Jimmy!

01:15:24.185 --> 01:15:25.675
There you go.

01:15:28.957 --> 01:15:32.154
<i>Braddock slides to his right,
tries cutting down the ring.</i>

01:15:41.870 --> 01:15:44.430
John, get off the ropes.
Move out of there.

01:15:44.506 --> 01:15:46.133
<i>Lewis spins his way
off the ropes</i>

01:15:46.207 --> 01:15:48.937
<i>And looks to resume control
at the bell!</i>

01:15:51.646 --> 01:15:54.945
There we go. Suck it up.
Deep breath.

01:15:55.016 --> 01:15:56.677
Deep breath, deep.

01:15:56.951 --> 01:15:59.511
All right. That ain't bad. He's
even faster than I remember.

01:16:00.088 --> 01:16:02.522
Yeah. He's fast. Big deal.
You're not so bad yourself.

01:16:02.590 --> 01:16:05.286
What are you doing? You
beat this guy easy last time.

01:16:05.360 --> 01:16:07.726
He ain't the same guy.
You got to use your speed.

01:16:07.795 --> 01:16:10.161
Keep that jab in his face
and keep sliding to his right.

01:16:10.231 --> 01:16:11.892
You see that.
Keep him in front of you.

01:16:11.966 --> 01:16:12.990
Cut him off, all right?

01:16:13.067 --> 01:16:16.093
And let go with the punches.
Hit him! He ain't gonna like it.

01:16:16.171 --> 01:16:19.231
I guarantee you, the more
you hit this bastard

01:16:19.307 --> 01:16:20.467
the slower he's gonna get.

01:16:20.542 --> 01:16:23.033
He's an old man. He's too
slow. He can't keep up with you.

01:16:23.111 --> 01:16:24.601
Come on. Use that jab.
How's that cut?

01:16:24.679 --> 01:16:25.668
He's all right.

01:16:25.747 --> 01:16:26.941
Knock the legs out
from under him.

01:16:27.015 --> 01:16:29.415
Trap him in the corner,
and really work him.

01:16:29.484 --> 01:16:31.042
Do not fight this fight his way.

01:16:31.119 --> 01:16:33.383
You make him fight
this fight your way!

01:16:33.454 --> 01:16:34.751
Let's go. You got him.

01:16:38.560 --> 01:16:41.154
<i>A left to the body
and a hard right to the head!</i>

01:16:41.229 --> 01:16:43.857
<i>A left-right-left by Lewis.
His dancing shoes are off.</i>

01:16:43.932 --> 01:16:45.399
<i>It's a fight now, folks!</i>

01:16:47.402 --> 01:16:49.131
Work his body, Jim!

01:16:49.204 --> 01:16:50.967
<i>Braddock punching well
with both hands now.</i>

01:16:50.989 --> 01:16:53.549
<i>Toe to toe!
No one giving an inch.</i>

01:16:56.661 --> 01:16:58.322
<i>That left has some pop!</i>

01:16:59.164 --> 01:17:01.758
<i>Jimmy's hoping those body shots
will pay dividends.</i>

01:17:02.567 --> 01:17:04.467
Keep him in there! Stay with him!

01:17:06.471 --> 01:17:08.996
Don't give him any room!
No room!

01:17:10.408 --> 01:17:11.841
Get out of the corner.

01:17:11.910 --> 01:17:13.935
<i>Braddock pushing
all the action now.</i>

01:17:14.012 --> 01:17:17.812
<i>Lewis can't discourage him.
Tremendous pressure from Jimmy.</i>

01:17:17.882 --> 01:17:21.409
<i>Lewis is running out
of real estate in this 24-foot ring.</i>

01:17:21.653 --> 01:17:22.813
Jump on him!

01:17:24.255 --> 01:17:25.916
<i>And Lewis is down!</i>

01:17:29.928 --> 01:17:31.555
Gotcha. Good boy.

01:17:31.629 --> 01:17:32.994
Get up!

01:17:34.165 --> 01:17:36.360
One. There you go, get up!

01:17:36.434 --> 01:17:38.425
Two.
Come on.

01:17:38.503 --> 01:17:39.902
Three.

01:17:40.805 --> 01:17:43.899
Four. Five.

01:17:45.577 --> 01:17:46.635
Six.

01:17:51.049 --> 01:17:52.414
<i>The referee wipes his gloves</i>

01:17:52.483 --> 01:17:54.007
<i>and Braddock steams
back to ring center!</i>

01:17:54.085 --> 01:17:55.382
Close it down.

01:17:56.221 --> 01:17:57.779
<i>Another big right by Braddock!</i>

01:17:57.855 --> 01:18:01.382
<i>Lewis is just a piece of meat
as Braddock is carving him up!</i>

01:18:03.228 --> 01:18:06.527
<i>Braddock is now dominating Lewis!
Here comes Jimmy!</i>

01:18:20.011 --> 01:18:21.876
Side to side!
Side to side!

01:18:22.046 --> 01:18:24.606
<i>In the tenth, riding high
after his dazzling victory</i>

01:18:24.682 --> 01:18:26.081
<i>over John Henry Lewis</i>

01:18:26.184 --> 01:18:29.017
<i>Jim Braddock has just hit
a wall named Art Lasky.</i>

01:18:32.657 --> 01:18:34.352
He can't keep taking
those body shots.

01:18:34.425 --> 01:18:36.825
I know. He's cracked
a couple of ribs for sure.

01:18:39.204 --> 01:18:40.865
<i>Lasky walks through
those jabs</i>

01:18:40.939 --> 01:18:42.907
<i>and keeps working
on Braddock's body.</i>

01:18:42.975 --> 01:18:44.567
<i>But Braddock won't fold!</i>

01:18:44.643 --> 01:18:47.908
<i>He's making Lasky work hard
for every minute of every round.</i>

01:18:48.514 --> 01:18:50.175
That's it, get on him!

01:18:53.485 --> 01:18:56.079
There you go, James!
That's it!

01:19:02.895 --> 01:19:05.125
<i>Lasky's starting to
impose his will.</i>

01:19:05.197 --> 01:19:07.597
<i>He's showing why Jimmy Johnston is
making noises</i>

01:19:07.666 --> 01:19:10.032
<i>about matching him
with Max Baer for the title.</i>

01:19:14.006 --> 01:19:15.405
Break it up!

01:19:16.241 --> 01:19:18.038
Come on. Break free.

01:19:19.445 --> 01:19:20.639
Break.

01:19:27.252 --> 01:19:29.652
Don't sit down. You're
not tired. You're fine.

01:19:29.722 --> 01:19:32.418
Get that thing out of here!
He don't need it!

01:19:32.491 --> 01:19:33.890
Is he looking over at you?

01:19:33.959 --> 01:19:35.984
Shake your head
like you don't need it.

01:19:36.061 --> 01:19:38.495
Shake your head like
you don't want it. There.

01:19:38.564 --> 01:19:41.362
Why isn't he sitting down?
Pay attention.

01:19:41.433 --> 01:19:42.730
Yeah, now he's gonna wonder:

01:19:42.801 --> 01:19:45.395
"If Braddock is such an old
man, why is he still standing?

01:19:45.471 --> 01:19:47.132
Why is he still
coming at me?"

01:19:48.207 --> 01:19:51.404
You're stronger than this guy.
Don't back up! Don't back off!

01:19:52.378 --> 01:19:53.538
This guy is a bull-rusher.

01:19:53.612 --> 01:19:56.479
He's gonna keep coming at you
all night until you stop him.

01:19:56.815 --> 01:19:58.578
He can't back up.
You stop him.

01:19:59.585 --> 01:20:01.416
You gotta beat
this son of a bitch!

01:20:01.487 --> 01:20:04.183
You gotta beat this son of
a bitch from the inside out!

01:20:04.256 --> 01:20:06.156
You hear me?
You gotta get in there.

01:20:06.225 --> 01:20:07.715
You get in there
and you hit him

01:20:07.793 --> 01:20:09.988
and you keep hitting him
until you break his nose.

01:20:10.062 --> 01:20:12.257
You fill his face with blood.

01:20:13.065 --> 01:20:16.364
Beat him from the inside
out, Jim! From the inside out!

01:20:16.902 --> 01:20:18.631
<i>Lasky continues to fire.</i>

01:20:18.704 --> 01:20:20.968
<i>Braddock looks like
he's finally starting to wilt.</i>

01:20:21.039 --> 01:20:22.939
That's it!
That's more like it!

01:20:25.177 --> 01:20:26.337
Back him up!

01:20:28.514 --> 01:20:30.709
<i>Lasky now looking
to put a Grimm ending</i>

01:20:30.783 --> 01:20:32.614
<i>to Braddock's
fairy-tale comeback.</i>

01:20:32.684 --> 01:20:34.618
<i>Lasky pounding hard shots
to the body.</i>

01:20:38.590 --> 01:20:40.581
<i>Braddock just took
a tremendous shot!</i>

01:20:40.659 --> 01:20:42.854
<i>A hard right to the head which knocked
his mouthpiece</i>

01:20:42.928 --> 01:20:44.088
<i>to the canvas.</i>

01:21:13.158 --> 01:21:15.490
<i>Braddock just took
Lasky's best shot!</i>

01:21:15.561 --> 01:21:17.119
<i>And it didn't even faze him!</i>

01:21:37.449 --> 01:21:39.246
Get in there
and take that sucker!

01:21:40.986 --> 01:21:43.113
<i>He's showing
tremendous determination!</i>

01:21:48.894 --> 01:21:51.055
Right in there
and get his nose!

01:21:57.636 --> 01:21:59.627
<i>Braddock comes in
with a hard shot to the body!</i>

01:21:59.705 --> 01:22:01.730
<i>The younger Lasky looks like
he's starting to wilt</i>

01:22:01.807 --> 01:22:03.798
<i>under the pressure from the Bulldog of
North Bergen.</i>

01:22:05.277 --> 01:22:06.835
<i>Braddock is now
back on the attack!</i>

01:22:07.813 --> 01:22:09.576
<i>Another vicious combination
by Braddock!</i>

01:22:09.648 --> 01:22:11.582
<i>And Lasky's flowing blood
from the nose!</i>

01:22:12.217 --> 01:22:14.082
<i>The 15th and final round.</i>

01:22:14.152 --> 01:22:16.143
<i>Braddock now looks
like the younger fighter</i>

01:22:16.221 --> 01:22:17.882
<i>and grimly determined.</i>

01:22:17.956 --> 01:22:20.823
<i>The Garden is on its feet!
Jim Braddock will not be denied!</i>

01:22:21.994 --> 01:22:25.225
<i>There's the bell! This one goes
to the scorecards.</i>

01:22:27.499 --> 01:22:31.458
<i>And the winner
by unanimous decision</i>

01:22:31.937 --> 01:22:34.269
<i>James J. Braddock!</i>

01:22:52.457 --> 01:22:53.947
Thanks, buddy.

01:22:57.963 --> 01:22:59.328
Max? What?

01:23:02.334 --> 01:23:04.097
Save a little bit of it

01:23:04.169 --> 01:23:05.830
Jimmy Braddock
just beat Lasky.

01:23:06.204 --> 01:23:07.865
They made him
the number one contender.

01:23:07.940 --> 01:23:09.635
Max, when are we gonna go to Shut up.

01:23:09.708 --> 01:23:11.573
Maxie, you
Shut up!

01:23:19.318 --> 01:23:21.786
I'm not gonna fight Jimmy
Braddock. He's a chump.

01:23:23.121 --> 01:23:27.387
You tell Johnston to bring me
somebody who can fight back.

01:23:27.993 --> 01:23:30.928
You gonna bust your contract?
It's done, Max.

01:23:43.575 --> 01:23:45.634
That's him? Yeah?
Yes, it is.

01:23:45.711 --> 01:23:47.645
I'm telling you. That's Braddock.

01:24:29.788 --> 01:24:31.278
Hey, Mrs. Braddock.

01:24:35.027 --> 01:24:36.460
Sara's here.

01:24:36.828 --> 01:24:38.318
Yeah?
Yeah.

01:24:38.397 --> 01:24:39.762
I got her to sleep.

01:24:41.299 --> 01:24:42.561
Hey, Jim.

01:24:44.936 --> 01:24:46.699
Mike's gone missing.

01:24:47.873 --> 01:24:49.170
How long?

01:24:50.942 --> 01:24:52.341
Three days.

01:24:53.011 --> 01:24:55.571
I've been staying at my
brother's since Jake cut him.

01:24:56.415 --> 01:24:58.940
Jake fired him?
I didn't know that.

01:24:59.151 --> 01:25:03.144
You know how Mike gets.
All his talk. So much trouble.

01:25:05.424 --> 01:25:07.892
He's been sleeping nights
down in the Hooverville.

01:25:08.460 --> 01:25:10.826
My brother didn't have room
for both him and us.

01:25:11.463 --> 01:25:14.455
Mike said, you know, if he had
to stay down there anyway

01:25:14.533 --> 01:25:17.058
he was gonna try
to get everybody organized.

01:25:18.270 --> 01:25:21.137
Something's
wrong, Jim. I know it.

01:25:22.274 --> 01:25:24.799
Now I'm hearing there's
some trouble in Hooverville.

01:25:25.644 --> 01:25:28.044
He wouldn't leave me
and the baby for this long.

01:25:29.781 --> 01:25:31.442
He just wouldn't.

01:25:32.684 --> 01:25:34.777
I didn't know
who else to come to, Jim.

01:25:43.361 --> 01:25:46.159
Come on, out of
the way! Beat it! Move along!

01:25:55.240 --> 01:25:57.674
Get the hell out of here, coppers!

01:26:00.112 --> 01:26:02.137
Mike? Mike Wilson!

01:26:04.382 --> 01:26:05.371
Mike Wilson!

01:26:08.487 --> 01:26:10.853
do nothing. If
you let these Commies in here

01:26:10.922 --> 01:26:13.857
and start a riot, then what
do you think's gonna happen?

01:26:14.426 --> 01:26:15.654
Get over here.

01:26:15.727 --> 01:26:16.716
On your feet!

01:26:17.395 --> 01:26:20.228
You pull a knife on me,
you son of a bitch?

01:26:24.903 --> 01:26:26.495
What the hell happened here?

01:26:26.571 --> 01:26:29.233
We tried to break up
these agitators, peaceful-like

01:26:29.307 --> 01:26:31.207
but they charged us.
What is this?

01:26:31.276 --> 01:26:33.369
The horses got spooked.
Wagons turned over.

01:26:33.445 --> 01:26:35.675
Three or four of them got run
over. They're hurt pretty bad.

01:26:36.248 --> 01:26:38.216
This is a
mess. One hell of a mess.

01:26:38.283 --> 01:26:40.843
What did I tell you?
Get back.

01:26:41.787 --> 01:26:44.119
Don't move those
two. Wait for the stretcher.

01:26:44.756 --> 01:26:46.781
