01:33:41.172 --> 01:33:43.800
Consider your
ass fully covered, okay?

01:33:47.378 --> 01:33:48.868
Run it again.

01:34:54.245 --> 01:34:55.974
Remember Ernie Schaaf?

01:34:56.047 --> 01:34:58.345
Nice guy. You
lost one to him in '31.

01:34:59.250 --> 01:35:01.514
Ernie took one of those
on the chin from Baer.

01:35:01.986 --> 01:35:03.578
He was dead
and didn't know it.

01:35:03.655 --> 01:35:06.647
Next fight, first little nothing
jab put him to sleep forever.

01:35:06.724 --> 01:35:08.123
Detached brain, they said.

01:35:11.029 --> 01:35:12.155
Joe?

01:35:13.498 --> 01:35:14.863
No snappy comeback?

01:35:17.001 --> 01:35:20.095
It ain't my skull the guy's
gonna try and stove in.

01:35:21.139 --> 01:35:22.128
You want to think about it?

01:35:24.976 --> 01:35:26.409
You think
you're telling me something?

01:35:28.313 --> 01:35:31.476
What, like, boxing's
dangerous, something like that?

01:35:33.685 --> 01:35:36.449
You don't think triple shifts or
working nights on the scaffolds

01:35:36.521 --> 01:35:37.954
is just as likely
to get a guy killed?

01:35:39.590 --> 01:35:42.650
How many guys died the other
night living in cardboard shacks

01:35:42.727 --> 01:35:43.785
trying to save on rent money?

01:35:44.796 --> 01:35:47.959
Guys who were trying to feed their
family. 'Cause men like you

01:35:48.032 --> 01:35:50.364
have not yet quite figured out
a way to make money

01:35:50.435 --> 01:35:51.766
out of watching that guy die.

01:35:51.836 --> 01:35:55.203
In my profession,
and it's my profession

01:35:57.141 --> 01:35:58.130
I'm a little more fortunate.

01:36:04.582 --> 01:36:08.177
All righty then. You guys
have dinner here tonight.

01:36:08.686 --> 01:36:10.119
Take your wives. It's on me.

